Standard metric cards for average latency, core threads, and sandbox uptime will also be integrated to provide a concise overview.\n\n**Implementing Interactive Filters**\n\nI'm now implementing the interactive filter state. I'm working to include a search input for agent names or IDs and a project filter dropdown for specific project views, such as Sovereign Core Sandbox 02. The goal is to provide comprehensive filtering capability within the system, using a dropdown.\n\n\n**Developing Filter UI**\n\nI'm now building the interactive filters. I've designed dropdowns for Agent Type, Status, and Operating Stage. These will filter the `previewAgentOperations` array. I'm focusing on enriching agent items with properties like `agentType` and `operatingStage` to enable fully functional filters. I'll construct a local, enriched agent list within the component to specify filter fields.\n\n\n**Defining Agent Display Data**\n\nI'm now defining the agent display data structure, enriched to support filtering and visualization. I've populated example agents with properties for name, project, status, type, stage, and key metrics. This enriched data will be used to generate agent cards, along with details like core threads, memory usage, logs, and more. I'm focusing on consistency in the data to ensure smooth filtering and sorting.\n\n\n**Refining Agent Card Structure**\n\nI'm now iterating on the agent card structure. I'm focusing on the display of core metrics like CPU, RAM, and latency, directly on the card to provide immediate insights. The data is prepped, so I'm now ensuring the card's visual hierarchy is clear. I'm thinking about including an uptime percentage as well.\n\n\n**Structuring Agent Tabs**\n\nI'm now creating the agent details tabs. I'm building tabs for 'Active Agents Telemetry', 'Task Queue', and 'Audit Logs'. I'm also preparing for the implementation of `activeAgentsTelemetry`, `taskQueue`, and `auditLogs`. I want to present these views in a clean and organized manner. I will be focusing on smooth integration with existing data.\n\n\n"}}
